Look at “lbs” as a variable, like the letter “x”. If you say 10x/5x, you will get 2. That’s because any number or variable divided by itself is equal to 1. So lbs/lbs is equal to 1. That’s how he got 2 instead of 2 lbs.

You actually divide 10 lb by 5 parts to get 2 lbs per part. You don't divide by 5 lbs, As an example, if you divide a 10 lb cake into 5 parts, you don't divide it by 5 lbs, but you divide it into 5 parts to get 2 lbs per part. Alternatively if you divide a 10 lb cake by 2lb then you get 5 parts and not 5 lb.  The 5 will be just a number without any units.. Or rather a 10 lb cake into parts of 5 lb, then you get 2 which is a number without any units attached.
